We are a "55+ Active Community" owned and operated by a family who brings over six decades of experience managing and operating communities in Florida and the Midwest. Printable Brochure Home is more than where you live Learn more about our family owned and operated community by clicking on the pictures below: View our current available homes If you’re ready to settle down, embrace an active community, and enjoy yourself, nothing beats owning your home. Owning a home provides a sense of stability and pride of ownership. At Swan Lake Village, we have a home for every homebuyer at the right price! CALL OR TEXT US NOW Find your perfect home today We have the right housing solution for you! Our homes are an excellent choice for an active retirement. Active 55+ Community Experience a unique sense of community and stability, where residents enjoy ACTIVITIES such as: “Sit and Be Fit” exercise classes Regular card games Weekly coffee hour Pot luck dinners Dances, luncheons, day trips, and the “Red Hatters” And don’t forget fishing in our beautiful lake where swans and other wildlife can be seen! LEARN MORE Exceptional amenities The Large Clubhouse is a “Community Hub” where neighbors can gather and enjoy the many activities including: Fitness room Billiard table Card tables Reading library Our clubhouse also has a large recreational room with a kitchen ideal for entertaining. It also has: Beautiful lake views A large lake where swans and other wildlife can be seen Heated Community Swimming Pool with a Large Pool Deck! Attractive Shuffleboard Center Our Community offers a “Sit and Be Fit” exercise class and card games to fit the active lifestyles of our residents. Our Community HOA coordinates weekly coffee hour, potluck dinners, dances, luncheons and numerous day trips. Great location BRADENTON provides easy access to major expressways and public transportation, as well as: Multiple dining, shopping and entertainment options. Close to several parks and some of the best beaches in the country! Many museums, performance arts centers, and galleries. We provide our residents with tips, amenities and a great social opportunity! LOCATION Bradenton Swan Lake Village is centrally located along Florida’s Gulf Coast in Manatee County, home to world-class beaches! We are 45 miles south of Tampa, Florida, conveniently located between downtown Bradenton and the City of Sarasota. The Community is 3 miles north of the famous resort town of Sarasota and 3 miles south of Historic Downtown Bradenton. The area boasts a high quality of life with year-round sunshine, a unique cultural heritage, beautiful sun-bleached beaches, a vibrant arts community, county-wide festivals, natural preserves and wildlife. Privacy Policy & Terms of Service - Swan Lake Village Swan Lake Village Swan Lake Village CALL US 941-205-6170 TEXT US Click here to send us an email Home About Our Homes Homes For Sale Great Location Testimonials EVERY QUESTION ANSWERED We care about your privacy Effective Date: 4/25/2025 Your privacy is very important to us. At Terrick Inc. DBA Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community we have a few fundamental principles that we follow: Although most changes are likely to be minor, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s sole discretion. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change. Website Visitors Thank you for using our text number services. We value your privacy, and this policy outlines how we  handle your data. Information We Collect Mobile Phone Number and email address: While on our website, through online applications, maintenance requests, showing requests, Tenant Web Access registration, site reservations, or general informational request forms we may collect your phone number to send and receive text messages. User-Provided Information: Any additional information you provide helps us improve our services and provide better support. How We Use Your Information Like most website operators, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community collects non-personally-identifying information of the sort that web browsers and servers typically make available, such as the browser type, language preference, referring site, and the date and time of each visitor request. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s purpose in collecting non-personally identifying information is to better understand how Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s visitors use its website. From time to time, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may release non-personally-identifying information in the aggregate, e.g., by publishing a report on trends in the usage of its website. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community also collects potentially personally-identifying information like Internet Protocol (IP) addresses for logged in users and for users leaving comments on our blogs. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community only discloses logged in user and commenter IP addresses under the same circumstances that it uses and discloses personally-identifying information as described below, except that blog commenter IP addresses are visible and disclosed to the administrators of the blog where the comment was left. We may also use your data to: Deliver text messages and updates related to our services. Improve our services and user experience. Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support. Occasionally send promotional offers, alerts, communication about community news, urgent  notifications, events, and other content. Certain visitors to Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s websites choose to interact with Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community in ways that require Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community to gather personally-identifying information. The amount and type of information that Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community gathers depends on the nature of the interaction. For example, we ask visitors who comment on our blog to provide a username and email address. For those who wish to receive Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community updates via email, we collect their emails. In each case, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community collects such information only insofar as is necessary or appropriate to fulfill the purpose of the visitor’s interaction with Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described below. And visitors can always refuse to supply personally-identifying information, with the caveat that it may prevent them from engaging in certain website-related activities. Message Content Messages may include promotional offers, alerts, communication about community news, urgent  notifications, events, and other content. Standard messaging rates may apply. Message frequency will vary. Data Security We take reasonable steps to protect your personal information from unauthorized access and disclosure.  However, no data transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we  cannot guarantee the absolute security of your information. No mobile information will be shared with third parties/affiliates for marketing/promotional purposes. All the above categories exclude text messaging originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with any third parties. Contact Us For questions or concerns about your data, please contact us by sending an email sales@swanlakemhp.com or Calling or Texting (888) 219-9780 CTIA Compliance Our services comply with CTIA guidelines. To report concerns or violations, contact us using the provided  information. Aggregated Statistics Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may collect statistics about the behavior of visitors to its websites. For instance, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may monitor the most popular pages on the www.swanlakemhp.net site or use spam screened by the Akismet service to help identify spam. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may display this information publicly or provide it to others. However, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community does not disclose personally-identifying information other than as described below. Protection of Certain Personally-Identifying Information Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only to those of its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations that (i) need to know that information in order to process it on Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s behalf or to provide services available at Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s websites, and (ii) that have agreed not to disclose it to others. Some of those employees, contractors and affiliated organizations may be located outside of your home country; by using Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s websites, you consent to the transfer of such information to them. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community will not rent or sell potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information to anyone. Other than to its employees, contractors and affiliated organizations, as described above, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community discloses potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information only in response to a subpoena, court order or other governmental request, or when Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community believes in good faith that disclosure is reasonably necessary to protect the property or rights of Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community, third parties or the public at large. If you are a registered user of an Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community website and have supplied your email address, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may occasionally send you an email to tell you about new features, solicit your feedback, or just keep you up to date with what’s going on with Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community and our products. We primarily use our various product blogs to communicate this type of information, so we expect to keep this type of email to a minimum. If you send us a request (for example via a support email or via one of our feedback mechanisms), we reserve the right to publish it in order to help us clarify or respond to your request or to help us support other users. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community takes all measures reasonably necessary to protect against the unauthorized access, use, alteration or destruction of potentially personally-identifying and personally-identifying information. Cookies A cookie is a string of information that a website stores on a visitor’s computer, and that the visitor’s browser provides to the website each time the visitor returns. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community uses cookies to help Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community identify and track visitors, their usage of Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community website, and their website access preferences. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community visitors who do not wish to have cookies placed on their computers should set their browsers to refuse cookies before using Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s websites, with the drawback that certain features of Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s websites may not function properly without the aid of cookies. Business Transfers If Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community, or substantially all of its assets were acquired, or in the unlikely event that Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community goes out of business or enters bankruptcy, user information would be one of the assets that is transferred or acquired by a third party. You acknowledge that such transfers may occur, and that any acquirer of Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may continue to use your personal information as set forth in this policy. Ads Ads appearing on any of our websites may be delivered to users by advertising partners, who may set cookies. These cookies allow the ad server to recognize your computer each time they send you an online advertisement to compile information about you or others who use your computer. This information allows ad networks to, among other things, deliver targeted advertisements that they believe will be of most interest to you. This Privacy Policy covers the use of cookies by Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community and does not cover the use of cookies by any advertisers. Comments Comments and other content submitted to Akismet anti-spam service are not saved on our servers unless they were marked as false positives, in which case we store them long enough to use them to improve the service to avoid future false positives. Privacy Policy Changes Although most changes are likely to be minor, Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community may change its Privacy Policy from time to time, and in Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community’s sole discretion. Swan Lake Village Manufactured Home Community encourages visitors to frequently check this page for any changes to its Privacy Policy. Your continued use of this site after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change. AdRoll When visiting our site, third parties (such as AdRoll) may place cookies on your browser for targeted advertising purposes. e.g. IP addresses, cookie identifiers or other tracking technologies such as pixels, and end-user website activity. Opt Out You can opt out of our messages at any time by replying “STOP” to a message. Reply “HELP” for more  information. Click the logo to learn more about interest-based advertising, who served the ad, and manage your ad options. You can also opt out of seeing personalized ads from AdRoll (and other companies) using the NAI opt out tool here .  Please note you will still see ads even if you opt out, but they will not be personalized by AdRoll. For more information please see AdRoll’s Privacy Policy .
